    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In India and elsewhere in South Asia, this term may describe people who are intersex, androgynous, transgender, or who have been born male, but adopt a female gender identity. Hijra people may be considered non-binary, that is neither male nor female, not associating themselves with a specific sexual orientation.</Note_Text>
